The paper focuses on software engineering research and the development of a rule mining system, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The use of data mining approaches for classification problems suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The development of a multi-objective algorithm suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of data from software repositories suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) category. Finally, the focus on iterative feedback from domain experts suggests that it could belong to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category.
